special_powers.name: EONS OF SCHEMING
special_powers.description: Empower, Enhancement, Probability Control.
Characters can't use the EFFECT of equipment.
Once per turn, each player may reroll a d6 in a friendly character's roll (including a single d6 in an attack roll).
Attack rolls of 1-1 are not critical misses. Attack rolls of doubles that would hit are critical hits.
When a character attacks, that character's controller gains 1 MISSION POINT for each time the attack roll is rerolled by an opposing effect.
When a standard character successfully breaks away, that character's controller gains 1 MISSION POINT (maximum 3 per turn).
When a character attacks, after resolutions deal them 1 penetrating damage for each 6 in the finalized attack roll.
When an opposing character uses Perplex, gain 1 MISSION POINT.
When a character uses Super Senses, increase the result of the roll by +1.
When a character uses Energy Shield/Deflection, modify their defense +3 instead of +2.
When a character uses Barrier, the markers don't need to be generated adjacent to each other.
When a character uses Mastermind, they may choose a friendly character within 6 squares instead of adjacent.
Characters that can use Regeneration may also use it as FREE.
When a character uses Invulnerability, reduce damage taken by 3 instead of 2.
Characters take a maximum of 2 damage from attacks.
When a character uses Flurry and misses one or both attacks, after resolutions they may make a close attack.
When a character uses Charge, they modify speed +2.
When a character uses Mind Control, after resolutions they may deal their printed damage value divided between all hit targets.
Characters can't use Improved Movement abilities. Characters that can use Plasticity have "FREE: Move at half speed."
When a character uses KNOCKBACK, they can knock back a character up to 6 squares instead of 3. If that character can use Force Blast, they can choose the direction of the knockback.
When a character uses Sidestep, they may move up to 3 squares instead of 2.
When a character uses Hypersonic Speed and hits during the action, after resolutions remove an action token from them.
When a character that can use Super Strength is given an action, after resolutions they may generate a standard object for them to immediately hold.
When a character uses Incapacitate, after resolutions they may deal their printed damage value divided between all hit targets that were given an action token.
When a character that can use Precision Strike makes an attack, that attack can't be evaded and damage taken from the attack can't be reduced below 2 instead of 1.
When a character uses Steal Energy, they heal 2 clicks instead of 1.
When a character uses Telekinesis, after resolutions remove an action token from them.
When a character attacks, its rolls of 10-11 are critical hits.
When a character hits with an attack roll of doubles, after resolutions remove an action token from them.
Hit characters have Battle Fury until your next turn, even if this card is not in play.
When a character that can use Exploit Weakness makes a close attack, after resolutions deal 1 penetrating damage to each opposing character adjacent to a hit target.
When a character uses Empower, also modify the attacker's attack +1.
The first time each turn Perplex is used, the chosen combat value is modified by +2/-2 instead of +1/-1.
The first time each turn Outwit is used, they choose two powers instead of one (on the same target character).
When a character uses Leadership, increase the result of the roll by +1.
When a character rolls for an effect using a single d6, increase the result of the roll by +1.
When a character damages an opposing character with an attack, after resolutions remove an action token from them.
